---
import Layout from "../components/Layout.astro";
import Header from "../components/Header.astro";
import Footer from "../components/Footer.astro";
---

<Layout
  title="Research & Advisory — Autonomy Bridge"
  description="Independent commercialization research for AI, robotics, industrial automation, and enterprise B2B SaaS. Market sizing, pricing validation, adoption risk, and commercial due diligence."
>
  <Header />

  <main class="container">
    <h1>Research &amp; Advisory</h1>
    <p class="subhead">Independent analysis for high-stakes technology decisions.</p>

    <section class="section">
      <h2>Commercialization Research</h2>
      <p>
        Commercialization research bridges the gap between "this technology works"
        and "this technology makes money."
      </p>
      <p>It focuses on:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Buyer economics and willingness to pay</li>
        <li>Adoption friction and deployment complexity</li>
        <li>Pilot-to-production conversion risk</li>
        <li>Unit economics under real-world constraints</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <h2>Research Products</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>Market Sizing &amp; Demand Analysis</strong> —
          Is the market large enough, and who actually has budget and urgency?
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Buyer Research</strong> —
          Who buys, how they decide, and what objections consistently block purchase.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Pricing &amp; Business Model Validation</strong> —
          What pricing model clears the market under real buyer constraints.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Competitive Landscape</strong> —
          Who else is playing, where they are weak, and what the defensible position is.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Adoption Risk Assessment</strong> —
          What blocks deployment, scale, or internal approval — before you find out the hard way.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Commercial Due Diligence</strong> —
          For PE and VC evaluating automation investments or portfolio company decisions.
        </li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <h2>How Engagements Work</h2>
      <p>
        Every engagement starts with a decision — not a topic. The deliverable is structured
        around what you need to decide, not what is interesting to research.
      </p>
      <p>
        Engagements are scoped with a defined output: a decision brief, market model, pricing
        framework, or due diligence assessment. No open-ended retainers. No deliverables without
        a decision at the end.
      </p>
      <p>
        <a href="https://calendly.com/deepak-autonomybridge" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
          Book a scoping call →
        </a>
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <h2>What We Don't Do</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Implementation, build, or integration work of any kind</li>
        <li>Market maps that tell you what you already know</li>
        <li>40-page slide decks with no decision at the end</li>
        <li>Ongoing retainers without a defined deliverable</li>
        <li>Anything where the answer has already been decided internally</li>
      </ul>
    </section>
  </main>

  <Footer />
</Layout>
